                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>In terms of pricing for using large language models, the number of tokens processed by the model typically plays a significant role. Many providers of LLMs offer pricing plans based on the number of tokens processed or the amount of computational resources used during inference.</p>
                                        <p>For example, if you're using a cloud-based LLM service, you might be charged based on the number of tokens generated by your prompts. Longer prompts or prompts that result in more tokens being processed may incur higher costs.</p>
